  "summary": "forge-jsx2@1.0.126 — multiple suspicious patterns require human review",
  "details": "The package contains several files with patterns that warrant manual review: a postinstall script (scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs) that performs network activity, a relay/upload module (dist/discordRelayUpload.js) with POST primitives and base64 decoding, secret-scanning code that fetches huggingface.co endpoints, and base64 decoding in a deployment defaults file (dist/deploymentDefaults.js) and an encode-deployment script. The package name has scope/typosquat-adjacent characteristics relative to forge/jsx ecosystems and ships a postinstall agent installer. While none of the matched primitives alone constitute conclusive proof of installer-side harm (base64 decoding, fetch to huggingface.co, and ping commands all have legitimate uses, and the relay-upload behavior may be a documented feature), the combination of a postinstall agent script, a 'discord relay upload' module, encoded deployment data, and a 'secret scan' module that performs outbound HTTP merits human inspection of the postinstall agent's actual behavior, the destinations of the relay/upload code, and what 'deployment defaults' is decoding before publishing a verdict.",
